headline: American Express Headquarters Move Tests Long Term Growth And Talent Plans
summary: American Express, NYSE:AXP, plans to build a new global headquarters at 2 World Trade Center in New York City. The project represents a major long term investment in the company’s presence in Lower Manhattan. The future headquarters is expected to feature modern, sustainable design and support the area’s continued revitalization. headline: All the highlights from Berkshire CEO Abel's first shareholder letter
summary: After two months on the job, new Berkshire Hathaway CEO Greg Abel emphasizes he won't be making major changes to the way the company has operated for decades under Warren Buffett's leadership.
